{"word":"ἀναίρεσις","slug":"ἀναίρεσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀναίρεσις</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀναιρέω'><el>ἀναιρέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a taking up</i> of dead bodies for burial, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—so, in a sea-fight, <el>ναυαγίων ἀν.</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>destruction</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>: <i>abrogation</i> of laws, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}